'''Jeffersonville Township''' is one of twelve [[Township (United States)|townships]] in [[Clark County, Indiana]]. As of the [[United States Census, 2000|2000 census]], its population was 56,695.

==Geography==
Jeffersonville Township covers an area of 26.84 square miles; 0.07 square miles (0.26 percent) of this is water. Brick House Pond and Silver Lakes are in this township.

===Cities and towns===
* [[Clarksville, Indiana|Clarksville]] (east three-quarters)
* [[Jeffersonville, Indiana|Jeffersonville]] (west three-quarters)
* [[Oak Park, Indiana|Oak Park]] (west three-quarters)

===Unincorporated towns===
* [[Arctic Springs, Indiana|Arctic Springs]]
* Blackiston Village
* Blooms Eddy (historical)
* [[Cementville, Indiana|Cementville]]
* [[Port Fulton, Indiana|Port Fulton]]
(This list is based on USGS data and may include former settlements.)

===Adjacent townships===
* [[Silver Creek Township, Clark County, Indiana|Silver Creek Township]] (north)
* [[Utica Township, Clark County, Indiana|Utica Township]] (northeast)
* [[New Albany Township, Floyd County, Indiana|New Albany Township, Floyd County]] (west)

